div.p: The physical definition of the User Interface and the available operations.
There are several "views" available during timer operations. The following diagrams describe the layout of data on the screen and the available actions for each input.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe flex-start; width: 264px; height: 1px; padding-top: 147px; margin-left: 187px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0px; text-align: left;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: none; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;

div.div:
User Input
There are a total of 7 pressable buttons:
- A
- B
- 4 direction pad (dpad)
- select (pressing in on the center of the dpad)
Visuals
Vertically centered between the dpad and A,B buttons is a color screen that is 135 pixels wide and 240 pixels tall.
User Experience
The buttons will control the operations of the timer and change the "view" presented.
Views will be accessible with the left and right dpad buttons. The views display the data associated with a session.
A session starts when the user presses the B button and continues until they press the B button again, starting a new session. Sessions do not need to be stopped.
